ance, the readings highlight how migrants have managed to actively resist these punitive practices. In bringing together critical theorists of immigration to understand how the current political landscape propagates the view of the "illegal alien" as a threat to social order, this text encourages students and general readers alike to think seriously about the place of undocumented immigrants in American society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh1 aDowling, Julie A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aInda, Jonathan Xavier, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478541940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804785419423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804785419.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles